[Method]
FindStringExact
[Prefix]
dcl_ComboBox_
[Desc]
This method finds the first string in a ComboBox that contains a list item with the exact string match without changing the ComboBox selection. A search for "Example Text" will find "Example Text". Use the dcl_ComboBox_SelectString function instead to both find and select a string.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
ProjectFileName
\par\tab SearchString
[as String]


[Method]
FindString
[Prefix]
dcl_ComboBox_
[Desc]
This method finds the first string in a ComboBox that contains a list item with the specified prefix or partial match without changing the ComboBox selection. A search for "Text" will find "Example Text". Use the dcl_ComboBox_SelectString function instead to both find and select a string.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
ProjectFileName
\par\tab SearchString
[as String]


[Method]
SelectString
[Prefix]
dcl_ComboBox_
[Desc]
This method finds the first string in a ComboBox that contains the specified prefix and selects this list item in the ComboBox.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
ProjectFileName
\par\tab SearchString
[as String]


